**1.**: _Find the dimensional formulae of the following quantities_ :

(a) _the universal constant of gravitation G,_

(b) _the surface tension S,_

(c) _the thermal conductivity k and_

(d) _the coefficient of viscosity_ n_._

_Some equations involving these quantities are_

\[F = \frac{Gm_{1}m_{2}}{r^{2}}, S = \frac{\rho g\ r\ h}{2}\,,\] \[Q = k\,\frac{A\ (\theta_{0}-\theta_{0})\,t}{d}\quad\text{and}\quad F = - \eta\,A\,\frac{v_{2}-v_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}\]

_where the symbols have their usual meanings._
**Solution :**: (a)_\(F = G\,\frac{m_{1}m_{2}}{r^{2}}\)_

or, \[G = \frac{F\Gamma^{2}}{m_{1}m_{2}}\] or, \[[G] = \frac{[F]\Gamma^{2}}{\text{M}^{2}} = \frac{\text{ML}\Gamma^{-2}\cdot\frac{\Gamma^{2}}{\text{M}^{2}}}{\Gamma^{2}} = \text{M}^{-1}\Gamma^{3}\Gamma^{-2}.\] (b) \[S = \frac{\rho g\ r\ h}{2}\] or, \[[S] = [\rho]\ [g]\Gamma^{2} = \frac{\text{M}}{\text{L}^{3}}\cdot\frac{\text{L}}{\text{T}^{2}}\cdot \frac{\Gamma^{2}}{\text{L}^{2}} = \text{MT}^{-2}.\] (c) \[Q = k\,\frac{A\ (\theta_{2}-\theta_{0})\,t}{d}\] or, \[k = \frac{Qd}{A(\theta_{2}-\theta_{0})\,t}\,.\]

Here, \(Q\) is the heat energy having dimension \(\text{ML}^{2}\text{T}^{-2}\), \(\theta_{2}-\theta_{1}\) is temperature, \(A\) is area, \(d\) is thickness and \(t\) is time. Thus,

\[[k] = \frac{\text{ML}^{2}\text{T}^{-2}\text{L}}{\text{L}^{2}\text{KT}} = \text{MLT}^{-3}\text{K}^{-1}.\] (d) \[F = - \eta\,A\,\frac{v_{2}-v_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}\] or, \[\text{MLT}^{-2} = [\eta]\text{L}^{2}\,\frac{\text{L/T}}{\text{L}} = [\eta]\frac{\text{L}^{2}}{\text{T}}\] or, \[[\eta] = \text{ML}^{-1}\text{T}^{-1}.\]
