Equilibrium of the block \(m\) gives \(T = \mu \rightleftharpoons V_{1}\) and \(\leftleftharpoons V_{1} = mg\) which gives \(T = \mu\, mg.\)... (i) Next, consider the equilibrium of the block \(M.\) Taking components parallel to the incline \(T + \mu \rightleftharpoons V_{2} = Mg\,\sin\theta.\) Taking components normal to the incline \(\leftleftharpoons V_{2} = Mg\,\cos\theta.\) These give \(T = Mg\,\left(\sin\theta - \mu\,\cos\theta\right).\) From (i) and (ii), \(\mu\, mg = Mg\,\left(\sin\theta - \mu\,\cos\theta\right)\) or, \(M/m = \frac{\mu}{\sin\theta - \mu\,\cos\theta}\) If \(\tan\theta < \mu\,,\,(\sin\theta - \mu\,\cos\theta) < 0\) and the system will not slide for any value of \(M/m.\)

