Consider any particle of mass \(dm\) on the ring, say at point \(A\). The distance of this particle from \(P\) is \(AP=z=\sqrt{a^{2}+r^{2}}\). The gravitational field at \(P\) due to \(dm\) is along \(\overrightarrow{PA}\) and its magnitude is

