**4.**: _Two wires of equal cross section but one made of steel and the other of copper, are joined end to end. When the combination is kept under tension, the elongations in the two wires are found to be equal. Find the ratio of the lengths of the two wires. Young modulus of steel = \(2 \cdot 0 \times 10^{\text{ 11}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}}\) and that of copper = \(1 \cdot 1 \times 10^{\text{ 11}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}}\)._
