**Solution**: **: The change in pressure** \[= \Delta P = 10^{\text{ 6}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}} - 10^{\text{ 5}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}}\] \[= 9 \times 10^{\text{ 5}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}}.\] \[\text{Compressibility} = \frac{1}{\text{Bulk modulus}} = - \frac{\Delta V/V}{\Delta P}\] \[\text{or}, 50 \times 10^{\text{ - 11}}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{2}}}\,\text{N}^{\text{\text{\text{1}}}} = - \frac{\Delta V}{(10^{\text{ - 1}}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}}) \times (9 \times 10^{\text{ 6}}\,\text{N}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{2}}}})}\] \[\text{or}, \Delta V = - 50 \times 10^{\text{ - 11}}\times 10^{\text{ - 3}}\times 9 \times 10^{\text{ 5}}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{\text{3}}}}\] \[= - 4 \cdot 5 \times 10^{\text{ - 7}}\,\text{m}^{\text{\text{3}}} = - 0 \cdot 45\,\text{cm}^{\text{\text{3}}}.\]

Thus the decrease in volume is 0 \(\cdot 45\,\text{cm}^{\text{\text{3}}}\).
