_Solution_ : When the light travels through a sheet of thickness \(t\), the optical path travelled is _m t_, where \(m\) is the refractive index. When one of the slits is covered by the sheet, air is replaced by the sheet and hence, the optical path changes by (_m_ - 1)_t_. One fringe shifts when the optical path changes by one wavelength. Thus, the number of fringes shifted due to the introduction of the sheet is

\[\frac{(\mu - 1)t}{\lambda} = \frac{\left( {1 \cdot 6 - 1} \right) \times 1 \cdot 8 \times 10^{-5}\,{\rm m}}{600 \times 10^{-9}\,{\rm m}} = 18.\]
